  "prompt": "Why does stars are not showing in my clash of clans map when I win on fighting with the other random players ?",
  "response": "In Clash of Clans, stars are typically awarded based on the percentage of destruction you achieve in an enemy base during an attack. If you're not seeing stars after winning a battle, there could be several reasons:\n\n1. Insufficient destruction: You may not have destroyed enough of the base to earn stars. Generally, you need to destroy:\n- 1 star: 50% of the base\n- 2 stars: 75% of the base\n- 3 stars: 100% of the base\n\n2. Technical glitch: Sometimes the game might have a minor bug affecting star display.\n\n3. Multiplayer battle issues: Ensure you're connected to a stable internet connection.\n\nTroubleshooting steps:\n- Check your destruction percentage after the attack\n- Verify your internet connection\n- Close and restart the app\n- Update the game to the latest version\n- Check if the issue persists in different battle modes\n\nIf the problem continues, you might want to contact Supercell support directly through the game or their official support channels.",
